        "row_9UgaCU": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "Training vs Match Gloves — Keep Them Separate",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">You wouldn't warm up in studs on concrete. Same logic applies here.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">We strongly recommend having one pair for training, one for match days. That way, your match gloves stay fresh, your grip stays elite, and you’re not walking into kick-off with latex that’s already been through the grinder.</p>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Train hard. Play harder. But don’t mix the two.</p>",
            "content-image": "shopify://shop_images/ba4d70ea203c43b3847bcc51cfd8b15afe07ceec.jpg",
            "content-isadaptive": false
          }
        },
        "row_gf7Qpi": {
          "type": "row",
          "settings": {
            "content-title": "How to Protect Your Match Gloves",
            "content-description": "<p class=\"section-content__text\">Want your gloves to show up every weekend? Look after them like they’re part of your kit — not an afterthought.</p>\n<ul class=\"section-content__list\">\n    <li class=\"section-content__elem\">Never train in them.</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Rinse after every match to clear dirt and sweat.</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Air dry — always. No heaters. No sun.</li>\n<li class=\"section-content__elem\">Store flat in a glove bag. No scrunching into the boot bag.</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"section-content__text\">Match latex is unforgiving. You take care of it — it’ll take care of you.</p>",
